# Real-Time Aggression Detection System ‚Äî Project Outline

## Overview

Build **AlertV** ‚Äî a real-time aggression/violence detection system that processes live or recorded video feeds, classifies frames as *aggressive* vs *non-aggressive*, and triggers alerts when violence is detected. The system will use deep learning (a fine-tuned CNN + LSTM or a 3D-CNN model) served behind a modern web dashboard.

---

## High-Level Architecture

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[üìπ Video Source<br>Camera / File] --> B[Backend<br>Python ¬∑ FastAPI]
    B --> C[ML Pipeline<br>Frame Extraction ¬∑ Model Inference]
    C --> D[Alert Engine<br>Threshold ¬∑ Notifications]
    B --> E[Web Dashboard<br>HTML/CSS/JS]
    D --> E
```

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| **ML / Video** | Python, OpenCV, PyTorch (or TensorFlow/Keras) |
| **Model** | Fine-tuned MobileNetV2 + LSTM *or* 3D-CNN (e.g. SlowFast, R3D) |
| **Backend API** | FastAPI (async, WebSocket support for real-time frames) |
| **Frontend** | Vanilla HTML + CSS + JavaScript (live video + alerts dashboard) |
| **Database** | SQLite (incident logs), optional Redis for real-time pub/sub |
| **Deployment** | Docker, optional cloud (AWS/GCP) |

